aboutSections.name: About
aboutSections.description: If you've never had this curry, you have been missing out for a long time. It is a beautiful curry with beautiful deep fried balls (koftas) of seasoned potatoes and paneer cheese. The experience of the koftas make this curry experience unique and unforgettable!

ingredients.name: Gold Potatoes
ingredients.measure: cup, cooked till just tender, mashed

steps.description: Simple combine all the ingredients of the spice blend into a bowl. You will use three-quarters for the gravy and a quarter for the kofta.
Add the diced onion to a large deep-dish pan with ripping hot smoking ghee. When the onions start to brown add the tomatoes and cook for five minutes
Add all the spices, cashews, and spice blend, and continue cooking until the mixture is very well reduced and the onions are almost a jam-like texture.
Blend all the ingredients with water or chicken stock until you form a very smooth paste
Add the mixture back to the cleaned pan with a lid and simmer for thirty minutes
Combine all the ingredients and form medium-bite-sized balls
Deep fry the balls in ghee or high smoke point neutral tasting oil at 350F until golden brown. Care for possible explosions!

Add the kofta balls on top of the curry, but do not submerge them as they will turn mushy. You can also serve them just on the side to prevent any kind of mushing. Serve with nice and garlic butter naan for an epic eating experience!
